. Other worries cropped up in the meantime. When I returned to Montreux in the beginning of August a landslide of correspondence had to be disposed of. And my butterfly net remains hanging on the branch of a fir at 1900 metres like Ovid's lyre.

I realize now that I shall not be able to realize our project in the "near future". We must cancel itâ€”or postpone it to a much later date.

With regret and gratitude,

yours

Vladimir Nabokov





